sec.p:
To assess the quality of the dataset to be used, our toolkit includes 2 functions for simulating datasets of different dimensionalities for stability assessment. We use those to understand the relation between the number of samples, genes, and cluster sizes. The first function simulates datasets, allowing for selecting the number of samples (n), genes (m), and clusters (c). Each cluster contains \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
